<TITLE> Teenage girl held on extremist charges in Kushtia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kushtia, Mar 23 (bdnews24.com)  A Kushtia court sent a teenage girl, suspected of being a member of an extremist group, to prison on Tuesday. Acting on a tip off, Kushtia police arrested 15-year-old Annana Islam Juthi at 8.45 pm on Monday from Mongolbaria Bazar of Kushtia town. She is suspected of being a member of the extremist outfit, Gono Mukti Fouz. Police asked for five days to interrogate her after presenting her at the court on Tuesday. The court set the next hearing to be on Wednesday and sent her to prison. Kushtia's additional police super CA Halim claimed that Juthi is a member of the extremist outfit and said that she is involved in transferring weapons and drug dealing. Kustia Sadar Police Station's OC Asaduzzaman said that she was interrogated at the station on Monday night following her arrest. He also said that Juthi's family had earlier filed a general diary claiming her to be a drug addict. At least seven women were arrested in the past six months from Kushtia on charges of involvement in extremist groups. bd
